comments.body:
I think this is wrong. While the docs use the example `stringKey`, `numberKey` and `booleanKey` it seems like the context is actually a map and you can use any key name you like.

```typescript
interface AuthResponseContext {
  [name: string]: string | number | boolean;
}
```

